ce:section.ce:para:
The viscoelastic properties of the HL-CNF and LL-CNF hydrogels (1-2 wt.%) obtained using HIUS processing at acoustic power of 51 and 53 W, respectively, were described by the elastic (storage) modulus G′, which is the reversible stored energy, and viscous (loss) modulus G″, which is the irreversible energy loss of the gel system (Fig. 2
                        ). The strain sweep test is a rheological experiment where the variation of elastic modulus (G′) and viscous modulus (G″) were monitored with the applied shear strain (

                              γ

                        ) (0.01-1000%) at a constant angular frequency (

                              ω

                        ) of 6.28 rad/s. The strain sweeps were executed to determine the linear viscoelastic region (LVR) and the onset ofnon-linearity, also known as critical strain % (


